@Guest513736147: the Jacob Van Lunen's story is my favourite of all times!   

This card costs like a hell, but with a severe control in the previous turns it's just an epic win! The fact that it costs so much means that it won't be overused like the others "Target player sacrifices a creature." cards, but it's in the late game that there are the biggest creature. You have to have other means to control the boards in the early game, but if you do everything right, at the end this is a powerhouse! Removal+draw isn't so common; removal+mass draw is almost unseen! (Ok, [Decree of Pain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Decree of Pain) is mass removal + mass draw, but it's the only one, I think... Edit: Even better: [Overwhelming Forces](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Overwhelming Forces)...)  

4.5/5

